17 SECTION 5. IC 36-7-1-1.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA CODE
18 AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE JULY
19 1, 2026]: Sec. 1.5. "Accessory dwelling unit" means a self-contained
20 living unit internal to or on the same lot or parcel as a single family
21 dwelling that:
22 (1) does not exceed the lesser of:
23 (A) seventy-five percent (75%) of the interior habitable
24 area (gross floor area) of the single family dwelling; or
25 (B) one thousand (1,000) square feet;
26 (2) includes its own cooking, sleeping, and sanitation facilities;
27 and
28 (3) complies with or is otherwise exempt from any applicable
29 building codes, fire safety codes, and other public health and
30 safety laws.
31 The term does not include a manufactured home (as defined in
32 IC 36-7-4-1106(b)) that is subject to the standards and
33 requirements set forth in IC 36-7-4-1106.
