18 of this chapter.
19 (b) A local authority shall review a permit application for
20 completeness. If a local authority determines that an application is
21 incomplete, the local authority must, not later than thirty (30) days after
22 receipt of the application, notify the applicant in writing of all defects
23 in the application. If a local authority fails to notify an applicant as
24 required under this subsection, the local authority shall consider the
25 permit application to be complete.
26 (c) An applicant that receives a timely written notice that an
27 application is incomplete under subsection (b) may:
28 (1) cure the defects in the application; and
29 (2) resubmit the corrected application to the local authority;
30 not later than thirty (30) days after receiving the notice. If an applicant
31 is unable to cure the defects within the thirty (30) day period, the
32 applicant shall notify the local authority of the additional time the
33 applicant requires to cure the defects.
34 (d) Subject to subsection (e), not more than ninety (90) days after
35 making an initial determination of completeness under subsection (b),
36 a local authority shall:
37 (1) review the application to determine if it complies with all
38 applicable requirements; and
39 (2) notify the applicant in writing whether the application is
40 approved or denied.
41 The local authority shall provide to the applicant the local authority's
42 written determination and findings of fact.
