31 Chapter 4.1. Permitted Uses; Parking, Lot Size, Density, Single
32 Stair and Elevator Requirements
33 Sec. 1. The definitions in IC 36-7-1 and IC 36-1-2 apply
34 throughout this chapter.
35 Sec. 2. This chapter does not apply to property within:
36 (1) a historic area or historic zoning district created under:
37 (A) IC 36-7-11;
38 (B) IC 36-7-11.1;
39 (C) IC 36-7-11.2; or
40 (D) IC 36-7-11.3; or
41 (2) a flood plain (as defined in IC 14-8-2-99).
42 Sec. 3. As used in this chapter, "affordable housing" means a
2026 IN 1001—LS 7120/DI 87

19
1 residential dwelling unit reserved for a household whose income
2 does not exceed eighty percent (80%) of the median income for the
3 area as set out by the United States Department of Housing and
4 Urban Development.
5 Sec. 4. As used in this chapter, "heavy industrial use" means a
6 storage, processing, or manufacturing use:
7 (1) with processes using flammable or explosive materials;
8 (2) with hazardous conditions; or
9 (3) that is noxious or offensive from odors, smoke, noise,
10 fumes, or vibrations.
11 Sec. 5. As used in this chapter, "mixed use residential" means a
12 development project that provides within a shared building or
13 development area:
14 (1) residential uses, including multiple dwelling units; and
15 (2) nonresidential uses that:
16 (A) comprise less than fifty percent (50%) of the total
17 square footage of the development; and
18 (B) are restricted to the first floor of any building
19 consisting of at least two (2) stories.
20 Sec. 6. As used in this chapter, "multi-family residential" means
21 a building designed to contain at least five (5) dwelling units that:
22 (1) are separated from each other by ceilings or walls;
23 (2) may not have interior doors through which access can be
24 made to other dwelling units; and
25 (3) may be accessible to each other through a common
26 hallway.
27 The term includes apartments and condominiums. The term does
28 not include a hotel, motel, or other transient lodging.
29 Sec. 7. As used in this chapter, "permitted use" means a use that
30 is approved by a unit in a zoning district without the requirement
31 of:
32 (1) a public hearing;
33 (2) variance, special exception, contingent use, or conditional
34 use; or
35 (3) other discretionary zoning action, other than a
36 determination that a site plan conforms with applicable
37 zoning regulations.
38 Sec. 8. As used in this chapter, "religious institution" means a
39 bona fide church, religious denomination, or religious organization
40 that is exempt from federal income taxation under Section
41 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code.
42 Sec. 9. (a) Notwithstanding IC 36-7-4 or any other law, the
